CSS rules are one type of so-called CSS statements.
The other types are At-rules that start with an at sign (@), followed by an identifier to say what kind of rule it is.
	@charset
	@import
	@media
	@document
	@font-face

Nested statements 
Example, applies the nested rule when the page's width exceeds 800 pixels.
	@media (min-width: 801px) {
	  body {
		 margin: 0 auto;
		 width: 800px;
	  }
	}
	